Bell Dance (new:गंप्याखं) is a [[Navadurga dance]] shown in [[Lalitpur District, Nepal|Lalitpur]] of [[Nepal]]. It is a traditional dance of the [[Newa people]] and religious for [[Hindus]].

==History==
The dance was started 346 years before was made form 2010.<ref>http://nepalmandalissues.blogspot.com/2010/10/blog-post_3119.html</ref> It was started by [[Malla period|Malla Kings]].

