[[Category:Critics| ]] [[Category:Art critics|*]] [[Category:Dance critics| ]] [[Category:Dance-related lists|Critics]] [[Category:Film critics| ]] [[Category:Film-related lists|Critics]] [[Category:Lists of people by occupation|Critics]] [[Category:Lists of visual art topics|Critics]] [[Category:Literature lists|Critics]] [[Category:Literary critics| ]] [[Category:Music critics| ]] [[Category:Music-related lists|Critics]] [[Category:Theatre critics| ]] [[Category:Theatre-related lists|Critics]]

In [[Argentina]] and other [[South America]]n countries, a '''''matinée''''' (also spelled '''matiné''') is a [[discothèque]] open to [[Adolescence|teenagers]] (usually between 14 and 18) before midnight. It was introduced in the 1990s because laws prohibited young people from going to dance in [[bar]]s and [[nightclub]]s that served [[alcoholic drink]]s.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}}

Throughout the 20th century up to the 1980s, the word ''matinée'' was used in Argentina for the first [[film]] exhibition of the day, usually around 2 p.m. and often intended for children.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} A ''matinée'' would usually feature a [[double feature]] of two films, with a live performance in between (usually a singer or comedy act) in the early decades of the century.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}}

A [[loanword]] to Spanish from French word ''matinée'' (in turn from the French ''matin'': 'morning'), the word was used in France (although not in its literal sense) to contrast from ''soirée'' (from ''soir'': 'evening') and from ''nuit'' ('night').<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://etimologias.dechile.net/?matine.-|title=Matiné|last=Vicente|first=Philippe|date=n.d.|website=Diccionario Etimológico español en linéa|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=November 11, 2018}}</ref>

==Features==
The usual age range is 14 to 18,{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} although some clubs admit 13-year-olds.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} The official schedule established by the [[Government of Argentina]] is from 8 p.m. to midnight;{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} in some provinces, the clubs must close by 11:30.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} The law prohibits smoking and alcoholic drinks.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} In practice, smoking is widespread.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} To circumvent the prohibition of alcohol, many young people drink at a friend's house or in a nearby park before heading to the matinee.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} Youngsters in Argentina call this the ''pre-boliche'' ("before the club").{{citation needed|date=November 2018}}

